Node.Notes: This verse apparently refers back to gn17:1. God made himself known to Abraham as El Shaddai, but not by his name Yahweh.
Uncertain. Most understand shortness of spirit as discouragement. Also possible impatience or exhaustion.
With other body parts indicates moral imperviousness to divine word (communication and understanding). Probably primarily inherent unfitness to transmit God's word (possibly impeded speech too).
Such a marriage is later forbidden for the Israelites in Lev 18:12 and 20:19, but is apparently culturally acceptable at this time.
